          <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#vlwgl">What information does a bank look at when giving loan?</a>
        </h4>
        <div id="vlwgl" class="collapse">
          <p>Loan is an amount which a person borrows from bank for a certain period of time and repays back after that time with interest rate.</p>
          <ol>
            <li>Secured loans</li>
            <li>Unsecured loan</li>
          </ol>
          <p><b>Secured loan:</b> A loan in which the person taking loan have to keep his/her property as guarantee to the lender in exchange for money.</p>
          <p>Ex., home loan, gold loan, car loan, business loan.</p>
          <p><b>Unsecured loan:</b> A type of loan in which the person who is taking loan do not have to keep a guarantee in exchange for money.</p>
          <p>Ex., student loan, personal loan, credit card.</p>
          <p>Bank when helping with loan they look at your credit score, income, ongoing EMI’s, occupation, repayment history, if secured loan bank will look for the value of the collateral, Size of down payment, purpose of loan.</p>
          <p></p>
        </div>
