        <h4 class="card-title">
          <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#dhmccaycsn">Does having multiple credit card affect your cibil score negativily?</a>
        </h4>
        <div id="dhmccaycsn" class="collapse">
          <p>No ,having multiple credit card does not affect your cibil score.</p>
          <p>Firstly what's a credit card it is like a post pay method of bank which we can use to pay for things and pay the bank afterwards monthly or in full.</p>
          <p>Cibil score is a credit score which is decided on the basis of your past and present payment history.</p>
          <p>Many of us are under the impression that shutting the old debit card and using the fresh one will improve their cibil score.</p>
          <p>But, it's false once the old card is been shut down along with it goes the credit points of yours .</p>
          <p>So, instead of shutting down you can limit the use of credit card and be regular with the repayment. So, it will help in bosting your cibil.</p>
        </div>
