        <h4 class="card-title">
          <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#wadtohl">What are different types of home loan?</a>
        </h4>
        <div id="wadtohl" class="collapse">
          <p>Let's discuss first what is a home loan, home loan is a type of loan which a person takes from bank to build himself a place called home.</p>
          <p>Home loan is a type of secured loan meaning it is given by the bank by taking a collateral or guarantee.</p>
          <p>There are a category of home loans between which you can choose based on your requirement:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Home construction loan</b></li>
            <p>This loan is like a gem for people who wants to construct their own house rather than buying an already constructed one.</p>
            <p>Before taking a construction loan one should know the exact cost of construction as the loan is based on the approximate construction cost. Construction loan also depends on the plot cost. The loan for construction loan is generally given in installments.</p>
            <li><b>Loan for purchase of loan</b></li>
            <p>The loan which is generally given to applicants who are looking to buy a land . And the person can give back the money in the form of monthly installments.</p>
            <li>Home expansion loan</li>
            <p>Thinking of expanding, adding a room or kitchen. This loan is the exact thing you may have been looking for as these loan is provided to applicants who just want to renovate or expand their existing home.</p>
            <li>Transfer of home loan</li>
            <p>Yes, you are hearing it right home loan can be transferred. But only when the conditions of the transfer of home loan is met which is if the owner of the property has sold the property to a new buyer. Generally the transfer of loan is also done if the person willing to transfer loan to another bank because he is finding a low interest rate on some other bank. But before transferring the loan one should keep in mind the processing fees etc.</p>
            <li>NRI home loan</li>
            <p>Most Indian bank provide secured home loan to NRI (non resident indian ). These loan is designed for NRI who want to buy a home in India. The procedure for these loans is slightly different from the others.</p>
          </ul>
        </div>
