        <h4 class="card-title">
          <a href="javascript:void(0)" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#hdigilwbc">How do I get instant loan with bad credit?</a>
        </h4>
        <div id="hdigilwbc" class="collapse">
          <p>Generally banks are willing to give an instant loan to person with a good credit score but does that mean a person cannot get loan if having a bad credit.</p>
          <p>The answer to this is no a person having bad credit can also get an instant loan.</p>
          <p>But with taking proper measures instant loan can be granted like.,</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Proving that you can repay with your income having a 5 digit salary does not mean you have a good cibil score but it can be a plus point in ensuring that you repay back the loan, so communicate with the lender and provide proof of steady income.</li>
            <li>Apply for a low personal loan. From a bank’s view low credit score means higher the probability to default in repayment. But if you take a low personal loan bank might get more assurance giving you the loan.</li>
            <li>Apply with a guarantor for loan Applying with a guarantor will get your chances of getting a loan more faster. But with getting a full permission with the guarantor.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>Getting a loan with bad credit score can get you a loan but the loan interest rate might be higher as the bad credit score directly indicates your bad repayment history.</p>
          <p>Bad credit score can be due to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Irregularities in repayment of EMI or credit card bills.</li>
            <li>Amount you took from bank.</li>
            <li>Having high credit use.</li>
            <li>New loan applied.</li>
            <li>Sometimes their might be an error in your cibil report which you need to discuss with bank.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>You can also boost your credit score by doing some healthy improvements to your account like.,</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Repaying your EMI or credit bills on time.</li>
            <li>Paying your credit card bills in full rather than monthly installments.</li>
            <li>Getting a mix of secured and unsecured loans.</li>
            <li>Controlling your credit card spending</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
